3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates TON/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC, based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.375% per cycle to prevent extreme payments. Long positions pay funding when rates are positive, while shorts receive payments, with settlements occurring automatically in USDT. Bitget's funding formula incorporates both interest rate components and premium index calculations to maintain price convergence."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","TON","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's high volatility and strong retail following frequently create funding rate imbalances, especially during ecosystem announcements or Telegram integration updates. The pair's substantial trading volume on Bitget ensures consistent liquidity for large arbitrage positions without significant slippage."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON/USDT funding rates on Bitget have shown distinct cyclical patterns, with positive rates dominating during bull phases when retail demand drives long bias. Historical data reveals funding rates frequently exceeding +0.1% per 8-hour cycle during major TON ecosystem developments. Weekend periods typically see reduced funding volatility due to lower trading activity. The pair exhibits strong correlation with broader L1 token funding trends but maintains unique spikes during Telegram-related announcements."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-exchange arbitrage between Bitget and other venues often yields 0.05-0.15% profit per cycle when funding differentials emerge. Delta-neutral strategies work effectively on TON/USDT due to Bitget's deep order books and tight bid-ask spreads. The 8-hour funding cycle provides sufficient time for position adjustments compared to exchanges with more frequent settlements. Calendar spread opportunities also arise during high volatility periods when different expiry months show funding divergence."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"TON's price volatility can create significant mark-to-market losses that offset funding gains, requiring careful position sizing and hedging. Bitget's relatively newer market presence means lower liquidity during extreme market stress compared to established exchanges. Auto-deleveraging risks increase during rapid TON price movements when margin requirements spike. Funding rate caps at ±0.375% can limit arbitrage profits during extreme market conditions when uncapped exchanges offer higher rates."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"What are typical TON/USDT funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"TON/USDT funding rates on Bitget typically range from -0.05% to +0.15% per 8-hour cycle, with higher positive rates during bullish periods. Extreme rates can reach the ±0.375% cap during major market events or ecosystem announcements."},{"question":"How does Bitget's TON funding compare to other exchanges?","answer":"Bitget's 8-hour funding cycles are longer than some competitors, potentially offering more stable arbitrage opportunities. However, funding rates may be less extreme due to Bitget's caps, which can limit profit potential compared to uncapped venues during volatile periods."},{"question":"What's the minimum position size for TON funding arbitrage on Bitget?","answer":"While Bitget has no explicit minimum for funding collection, practical arbitrage typically requires positions worth $1,000+ to overcome trading fees and spread costs. The 0.02% maker fee means smaller positions may not generate sufficient funding to cover transaction costs."},{"question":"Can I use Bitget's copy trading for TON funding strategies?","answer":"Bitget's copy trading feature can be used for funding rate strategies, but most profitable approaches require active management and quick position adjustments. The 8-hour funding cycles provide enough time for manual oversight, making copy trading less critical than for higher-frequency strategies."}]}]
